<P>Lord, I am not only guilty, but polluted; Sin hath as well defiled me, as it would con|demn me Lord, I have a heart as black as Hell, as fil<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">hy and unclean as the unclean Spi|rits them&s;elves; but is not here blood to wa&s;h <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word">, as well as pardon me? To purge me from my filth, as well as &s;ave me from the guilt of all my &s;in? To this clean&s;ing blood <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> bring my defiled Soul, and I will believe <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">hat thou wilt wrince, and make me clean. Lord, here is blood, and what may hinder, but may wa&s;h and be clean?</P>
