<P N="1">1. Sometimes I would think upon the Love of God and Chri&s;t. 2 Som<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">times upon his Wrath and Sev<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">rity again&s;t Sin. 3. The <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> nature of &s;in. 4 The preciou&s;ne<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> of my Soul. 5 The &s;uff<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ri<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">gs of my Lord. 6 Of my &s;itting with God in his Kingdom. An<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> 7 The priviledges I am made partaker of in <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">his lif<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> by the de<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">th o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Chri&s;t.</P>
